    <subsection>
       <theorem>
        <title>Factor Theorem</title> 
        <statement> 
          <p> A number c is a zero of a polynomial function f(x) if and only if 
             x-c  is a factor of f(x).</p>
        </statement>
      </theorem>
      <theorem>
        <title>Fundamental Theorem of Algebra</title> 
        <statement> 
          <p> A polynomial function f of degree n > 0 has at least one zero.</p>
        </statement>
      </theorem>
    <title>Activities</title>
  

    <activity xml:id="activity-4-1">
      <introduction>
        <p>Write the polynomial function in factored form using information from the graph below.</p>
     
      <figure xml:id="fig-sage-graph">
        <image>
            <sageplot>
            f(x)=(((1/80)*(x-3))*((x+4)^3)*(x^2))
            p=plot(f,(x,-6,6),ymin=-20,ymax=20,color='blue',thickness=3)
            p
            </sageplot>
        </image>
    </figure>
  </introduction>
      <task> <p>Using the given graph, what are the real zeros of this function? Select all that apply.
       <ol marker= "A."><li> 0</li>
        <li> 1</li>
        <li> -3</li>
        <li> 3</li>
        <li> 4</li>
        <li> -4</li></ol>
      </p>
      </task>
      <task> <p>What are the least possible multiplicities for each zero? 
      </p>
      </task>
    <task><p>What is the least degree of the function?
      <ol marker= "A."><li> 3</li>
